BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:li5gtbUlv8gBof3yq3HCG
SUMMARY:Coworking Tuesdays
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260310T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday Cowork \\+ Coffee/Tea \\(Weekly\\) \n\nNeed a reason to
	 get out of your inbox cave and into a productive\, low-pressure space? Jo
	in us every Tuesday for a drop-in coworking morning—bring your laptop\, kn
	ock out your priorities\, and enjoy the energy of working alongside other 
	local professionals. \n\nWhen: Tuesdays | 9:30–11:30 AM | No registration 
	needed\n\nFormat: Come for the full two hours or pop in when you can\n\nWh
	o it’s for: Business owners\, remote workers\, creatives\, students\, nonp
	rofit leaders—anyone who wants focused work time \\+ light community\n\nWh
	at to expect: Quiet “get-it-done” work blocks\, optional hellos \\+ quick 
	intros\, and a friendly vibe \\(no forced networking\\) \n\nLocation \\(th
	rough February\\): Bothell Visitor Center\n\nWe’ll rotate locations monthl
	y—same time\, same Tuesday rhythm\, fresh spaces. \n\nBring: Your laptop \
	\+ whatever you need to work. We have the coffee\, tea\, and water!\n\nQue
	stions? Email sandra@bothellkenmorechamber.org\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/coworking-tuesdays/17806278/2026-03-10T00\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/coworking-tuesdays/178062
	78/2026-03-10T00
LOCATION:Bothell Kenmore Chamber\, 10031 Main Street\, Suite A\, Bothell\, 
	WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4Rk_Jq_xmjgUlWrSPNUhE
SUMMARY:Tea with T: Informational Webinar on WEBS
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260310T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description    Tea with T: How to Use WEBS Tuesday\, March 10 |
	 10:30 AM PT | Zoom Join GSBA for Tea with T\, an informational webinar le
	d by Toraya Miller\, where we'll walk through Washington's Electronic Busi
	ness Solution \\(WEBS\\) and how to register and use it to find state cont
	racting opportunities. Bring a cup of tea and get set up in 5-10 minutes s
	o bid opportunities that match your commodity codes can start coming strai
	ght to your inbox. What is WEBS? Washington's Electronic Business Solution
	 \\(WEBS\\) is an internet-based bid notification system hosted by the Dep
	artment of Enterprise Services \\(DES\\). Many state agencies and educatio
	nal institutions use WEBS to notify businesses of contracting opportunitie
	s based on the commodity codes you select.   About Toraya Miller Director 
	of Training & Consulting\, GSBA Toraya Miller leads GSBA's training and co
	nsulting work\, supporting businesses across Washington as they navigate g
	rowth\, certification\, and public-sector opportunities. In this session\,
	 Toraya will guide participants through WEBS and share practical tips for 
	getting registered\, staying updated\, and using the system to identify co
	ntracting opportunities with the state. In this webinar\, we'll cover: ☕ W
	hat WEBS is and why it matters for vendors ☕ How to register as a vendor i
	n WEBS ☕ How to choose and update your commodity codes ☕ Where to find cur
	rent and upcoming bid opportunities ☕ How to use forecasted purchases to p
	lan ahead ☕ Tips to keep your profile updated so opportunities keep brewin
	g Learn more about WEBS Washington Department of Enterprise Services: Bid 
	Opportunities \\+ WEBS\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/te
	a-with-t-informational-webinar-on-webs/18089675/2026-03-10T00\n\nFrom SEAt
	oday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tea-with-t-informational-
	webinar-on-webs/18089675/2026-03-10T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
